{"questionId":"9066350","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Ethyne, C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub>, reacts with oxygen in welding torches.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Ethyne reacts with steam.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub> (g) + H<sub>2</sub>O (g) → C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>O (g)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Two possible products are:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/5980/4c.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"316\" height=\"190\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Deduce the splitting pattern you would expect for the signals in a high resolution <sup>1</sup>H NMR spectrum.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">2.3 ppm:</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">9.8 ppm:</span></span></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">2.3 ppm: doublet &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">9.8 ppm: quartet &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066350","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ2.c(v)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the splitting pattern you would expect for the signals in a high resolution 1H NMR spectrum. 2.3 ppm: 9.8 ppm:","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(v)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 21: Measurement and analysis","21.1 Spectroscopic identification of organic compounds","Additional highe